Note: this has been edited

Would you please verify whether or not the following resources exist for the Home machine:

{{"C:\ProgramData\Titanium\mobilesdk\win32\1.8.0.1.v20111116130058\android\avd.py"}}
{{"C:\Program Files (x86)\Android\android-sdk\"}}

Thanks

Just to confirm, the home machine is running 64bit Windows 7, isn't it?

Would you please run the following two commands, to verify that they are working correctly? Both should output the usage statement.

{code:lang=none}
C:\>python ProgramData\Titanium\mobilesdk\win32\1.8.0.1.v20111116130058\android\avd.py
C:\>python ProgramData\Titanium\mobilesdk\win32\1.7.5\android\avd.py
{code}

Hi Paul, I think I've had the same problem. I solved it by disabling the check for standard error output in run.py.

I changed line 39 in run.py from

if type(se) != types.NoneType and len(se) > 0:

to

if False and type(se) != types.NoneType and len(se) > 0:

Now it can detect the android sdk an I can select the android version.
